description: The Secret Service and the Trump campaign say the former president is 'safe' following a shooting nearby in Florida.
title: Gun shots fired near Trump at his Florida golf course, former president is 'safe'

description: The top legal adviser to New York City Mayor Eric Adams resigned over the weekend, the latest sign of instability in the Democrat's administration as it deals with multiple federal investigations.
title: Top legal adviser to New York City mayor quits as investigations swell

description: Sen. JD Vance, in a media appearance, blames the media for ignoring the situation in Springfield, Ohio, and justifies false stories about Haitian migrants.
title: Vance defends spreading claims that Haitian migrants are eating pets

description: Seven months have passed since South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol announced a plan to increase the number of doctors. Trainee doctors walked off their jobs in protest and they haven’t returned.
title: As medical strike drags on in South Korea, patients are on edge

description: Torrential rains in Central Europe have forced massive evacuations in the hardest hit areas in the Czech Republic, where floods reached extreme levels on Sunday.
title: Torrential rains trigger mass evacuations as rivers surge in Central Europe

description: While lots of powerful changes to reduce food waste can start at home, sometimes the scale of the problem benefits from a community-wide approach.
title: Creative ways communities are reducing food waste

description: Finding meals that are good for you, your wallet and the environment can be difficult. We've pulled together a few recipes to make sustainable choices even easier.
title: Not sure what to make for dinner? Here are recipes to help you eat sustainably

description: Climate researchers have long grappled with how to get Americans to eat less beef, a food with a huge global warming impact. Now some are thinking about it through the lens of gender.
title: Eating less beef is a climate solution. Here's why that's hard for some American men

description: Around a third of women of reproductive age could have low iron. But doctors don’t routinely screen for the condition, though it can lead to anemia. Symptoms include exhaustion, headaches and more.
title: Exhausted? Irritable? It could be undiagnosed iron deficiency

description: Research shows that a toxic mix of past traumas and the stresses of resettlement puts refugee kids at significantly higher risk of long term mental health challenges. A new effort aims to mitigate those risks by supporting parents and children in refugee families.
title: How do you help young Afghan refugees heal? A new program in Maine offers a way

description: Hillary Clinton leaned into her identity when she ran for president. Vice President Kamala Harris is decidedly not.
title: If Harris wins, she would make history. But she isn’t talking about that

description: Much of the food supply in the U.S. goes uneaten, which contributes to climate change. Some states have tried to cut food waste in landfills, but their efforts have fallen short, researchers found.
title: State bans on commercial food waste have been largely ineffective, study finds

description: Three Americans, two Spaniards and a Czech citizen were arrested after Venezuelan officials accused them of coming to the South American country to assassinate President Nicolas Maduro.
title: Venezuela says it arrested 6 foreigners allegedly involved in a plot to kill Maduro
